    "causal_summary": "A document can carry curated `answerable_questions` and `semantic_intent` tags that name the queries it should win and the intent class it serves, but those tags are inert today. The frontmatter extractors in `memory-parser.ts` only pull a fixed set of known fields (`trigger_phrases` at L785-863, `content_type` at L864, `importance_tier` at L880), so an `answerable_questions` field persists on disk and is silently dropped from the vector and the metadata payload. The fusion stage in `stage2-fusion.ts` consumes only `validationMetadata.qualityScore` and a few spec signals (L260-289), so even if the tags reached the row there is no consumer to read them. This is the 028 dead-field trap: a field that exists on the JSON surface but never moves a single retrieval result.",
